1. Which of the following steps must you take to create your own thread class?
Ans:
- You must create a custom run function.
- You must instantiate your new thread class.
- You must extend the Thread class.

2. Implementing a Runnable interface is a more lightweight method to create a secondary thread.
Ans: True

3. Call the interrupt method on the thread object to explicitly interrupt a thread that is already running.
Ans: True

4. Synchronizing your threads means they all run at the same time.
Ans: False
